## FAQ

**Q: Can I use non-standard components (e.g., custom attention variants, gating mechanisms, novel normalization)?**
A: Yes, as long as (1) you specify them precisely enough that David can implement them, (2) they fit in the simulator export format, and (3) they train within the VRAM constraint. If the simulator doesn't natively support a component, describe it in the design document with enough detail to implement.

**Q: Can I use a mixture-of-experts architecture?**
A: Yes, but the total parameter count (including all experts) must be under 500M, and it must fit in 16 GB VRAM during training.

**Q: What if my chosen corpus needs preprocessing?**
A: Specify the exact preprocessing steps in your design document. Keep it reasonable — David shouldn't need to spend a week cleaning your data. Use a well-known dataset with a well-known preprocessing pipeline.

**Q: Is there a minimum parameter count?**
A: No. If you can justify a 50M model that you believe will outperform larger ones in 7,500 steps, go for it. Efficiency is rewarded.

**Q: What framework will training use?**
A: PyTorch. If your design requires specific framework features, note them in the design document.

